Goal: Rapidly iterate 3D-printable parts with minimal tokens.

Status (current assets):
- card/ — denomination cards (STLs) + snug variant generator
- maple_auto_1oz_total/ — maple-themed plaques (STLs)
- tp_rod/ — fixed-length rod generator

Guidelines:
- Keep prompts short; prefer deltas from existing STLs.
- State functional constraints, target dimensions, tolerances, printability.
- Ask for parametric source (OpenSCAD or Fusion parameters) when possible.

House style:
- Units in mm; specify wall/perimeter targets if relevant.
- Fillets/chamfers for strength; avoid overhangs > 45° unless supported.
- Labeling: embossed text ≥ 0.6 mm height, 0.4 mm stroke.

Output expectations:
- If generating code: OpenSCAD preferred; otherwise a concise step-by-step CAD plan.
- Provide a final STL export list and any print orientation notes.
